        {
            "_id": "XD6xUWuF0jao8qp4",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Agonizing Welts",
            "sort": 1200000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Jinnivere can wield her riding crop as a melee weapon to create agonizing pain in the minds of those she strikes. It also inflict a curse that causes their mental pain to manifest as painful visible welts and seeping wounds that never seem to heal. If she inflicts agonizing welts on a creature already afflicted by it, the victim attempts a new save, ignoring the result if it's better than a failure.</p><hr /><p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[fortitude|dc:26]</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} and all speeds are reduced by 10 feet (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> As stage 2, except @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 3} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> As stage 2, except clumsy 3 and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} (1 round)</p>"
                },
